JavaScript engines are used in web browsers, servers, and other applications that need to run JavaScript code. The most popular JavaScript engines are V8 (used in Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge), SpiderMonkey (used in Firefox), and JavaScriptCore (used in Safari).\par
JavaScript engines are typically developed by web browser vendors, and every major browser has one\par

